you think might have helped you or been 
inspirational? who maybe took particular pains

21:57.580 --> 22:03.747
with you, or any that you had a close relationship 
that you recall? I would think in the EE

22:06.310 --> 22:27.115
department, of course,

22:06.310 --> 22:27.115
LL Four Acre was probably one that,

22:06.310 --> 22:27.115
don't know if it's necessarily inspiration, but 
more understanding of some of your problems and

22:06.310 --> 22:27.115
this and than any I had, and I had him, I guess, as 
sophomore and junior on some courses. You, in the

22:36.698 --> 22:47.127
department at that time, of course, Rhodey was one 
who was, always amazed you.

22:51.030 --> 22:56.595
He could ride around the room about three times 
during a one-hour class. Let's get back a little

22:58.938 --> 23:01.360
bit. Do you remember any impressions about the 
campus when you got there? What you felt about the

23:05.143 --> 23:09.968
whole physical nature of it? Was it over, was it 
friendly?

23:14.992 --> 23:17.775
Or was it a stark sort of place? No, it was, of 
course, we lived in, at that time, the new dorms,

23:18.195 --> 23:27.443
the 1 to 12.

23:29.279 --> 23:40.476
I'd always thought

23:29.279 --> 23:40.476
that the campus was well landscaped and they 
